<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.1.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-04-02T01:05:29+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">sakkamade</title><subtitle>through a life with yuri in heart</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ③</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/31/witches-2-3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ③" /><published>2021-03-31T02:17:41+00:00</published><updated>2021-04-01T21:52:21+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/31/witches-2-3</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">I lay a question upon her tearful self:</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ②</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/27/witches-2-2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ②" /><published>2021-03-27T21:29:42+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-30T19:51:25+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/27/witches-2-2</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">“It was a terrible day.”</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ①</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/24/witches-2-1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 2. Forgotten Witch. ①" /><published>2021-03-24T03:26:21+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-30T19:52:03+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/24/witches-2-1</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">Late at the night enclosed by the park, I was seated upon a swing alone, whereas staring downwards.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑦</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/21/witches-1-7" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑦" /><published>2021-03-21T03:21:08+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-30T19:52:49+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/21/witches-1-7</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">“Good joke, Tsugu! It’s me, Rino—Honda Rino!” “Uh, um—.” “In days of our sharing a middle school, we have had bouts of witchcraft often times! I am your rival: Rino!”</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑥</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/18/witches-1-6" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑥" /><published>2021-03-18T02:45:48+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-30T19:58:16+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/18/witches-1-6</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">Maejima-san swiped the screen of her phone. These are pictures of a fish swimming. Not within, however, swimming without the water tanks. She has taken a numerous pictures of fish of nonexistent, vivid shades, which were set in an impracticable travel. Among them, there also was a photo of director and myself. Photo-testimony. The scene of a crime. Conclusive evidence.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑤</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/15/witches-1-5" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ⑤" /><published>2021-03-15T02:12:43+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-18T19:31:54+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/15/witches-1-5</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">I opened my eyes. How long have I been asleep, I asked myself. I should not have worked much, and yet I wonder if I had grown fatigued?</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ④</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/12/witches-1-4" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ④" /><published>2021-03-12T04:09:26+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-18T19:29:51+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/12/witches-1-4</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">I can’t help it, eh.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ③</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/05/witches-1-3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ③" /><published>2021-03-05T02:37:15+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-18T19:25:43+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/05/witches-1-3</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">“Nothing, whatsoever…”</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ②</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/02/witches-1-2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ②" /><published>2021-03-02T18:35:21+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-18T19:24:15+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/03/02/witches-1-2</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">When I woke up, I felt as though being under the water. It was a little distinct a sensation of sinking below the water surface, or of deep-sea fish. Whereas suffocating, I cannot arise upwards. Whilst screaming out, my voice does not reach anywhere. The light is far away, I struggle, but my body is too heavy. When, at the end, “Oh, well,” I find myself compromising amid that space. Upon some place, however, I would interrupt myself. Saying: “It’s no good!” That myself then would cast a spell upon me. Saying: “I wish today you will be the best of myself.”</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Section 1. Flightless Witch. ①</title><link href="https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/02/27/witches-1-1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Section 1. Flightless Witch. ①" /><published>2021-02-27T21:27:24+00:00</published><updated>2021-03-18T19:23:12+00:00</updated><id>https://sakkamade.github.io/2021/02/27/witches-1-1</id><author><name>sakkani</name></author><category term="Para Witches" /><category term="webnovel translation" /><summary type="html">It is paradoxical.</summary></entry></feed>